# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OpenRouter API key (PRIMARY — recommended)
# 100% free forever, no billing required, works in all regions.
# Get your key at https://openrouter.ai/keys
# The chat backend uses OpenRouter's free models (e.g. openai/gpt-oss-120b:free)
# as the primary chat backend, with automatic fallback to Gemini/Z.AI on errors.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Gemini API key (SECONDARY fallback)
# Used automatically if OpenRouter is rate-limited or down.
# Note: Gemini API is region-restricted. If you see
# "User location is not supported for the API use" errors, enable billing
# on your Google Cloud project or just rely on OpenRouter instead.
# Get your key at https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GEMINI_API_KEY=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Z.AI API key (LAST RESORT fallback + required for web search & image gen)
# Used as the final chat fallback if both OpenRouter and Gemini fail.
# Also required for /api/agent/search and /api/agent/image routes (Z.AI
# provides the specialized web_search and image generation functions that
# neither OpenRouter nor Gemini expose directly).
# Note: Z.AI chat requires paid quota. Web search & image gen may also
# require balance — check at https://open.bigmodel.cn/usercenter/apikeys
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ZAI_API_KEY=""

# Legacy alias. Older deployments may have set this instead of ZAI_API_KEY.
# SARVAM_API_KEY=""

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Database (optional — only needed if you actually use Prisma features)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@host:5432/dbname"

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Agent service (mini-services/agent-service) — optional overrides
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Port the Socket.IO agent service listens on. Default: 3003.
# AGENT_SERVICE_PORT=3003

# Path to the agent-browser CLI. Defaults to "agent-browser" (resolved via $PATH).
# AGENT_BROWSER_PATH="/usr/local/bin/agent-browser"
